David Bazan - Fewer Moving Parts (2006)(FLAC)










David Bazan (born January 1976) is an indie rock singer-songwriter from Seattle, Washington. Bazan (pronounced &quot;buh-zahn&quot;) was the lead singer and creative force behind the now-defunct band Pedro the Lion and was the lead singer of Headphones, a band he formed out of his interest in synthesizers. In early 2006, he began performing and recording under his own name.

